WEBVTT

00:01.135 --> 00:02.703
(male #1)
Here's a little test for you.

00:02.770 --> 00:06.440
What medical drama about doctors
working in a children's hospital

00:06.507 --> 00:08.642
has been on television
the longest?

00:08.709 --> 00:12.080
Well, if you'd said anything
other than "Childrens Hospital"

00:12.146 --> 00:15.349
or "Kid Emergency Room",
you'd be wrong.

00:15.416 --> 00:17.051
But that's all
about to change.

00:17.118 --> 00:20.521
Because after fifteen
long years on the air..

00:20.588 --> 00:23.924
..."Childrens Hospital"...
is pulling the plug.

00:23.991 --> 00:27.528
I almost forget what I look like
without the makeup on, you know?

00:27.595 --> 00:30.998
(male #1)
'And later on in the program,
dolphins have long been deride''

00:31.065 --> 00:33.000
'as poor man's tuna.'

00:33.067 --> 00:35.336
'Not quite fish,
not quite mammal.'

00:35.403 --> 00:36.937
I'm Louis La Fonda.

00:37.004 --> 00:41.475
All that and Andy Rooney
tonight...on "Newsreaders".

00:41.542 --> 00:43.477
[dramatic music]

00:51.419 --> 00:53.721
For the cast and crew
of "Children's Hospital"

00:53.787 --> 00:56.624
and its many fans,
next Friday at 10:30 pm

00:56.690 --> 00:58.892
marks the end of an era.

00:58.959 --> 01:02.530
That's when the final episode
airs for the first time.

01:02.596 --> 01:06.300
In one sense,
a victim of its own success.

01:06.367 --> 01:11.572
But in another more real sense,
a victim...of low ratings.

01:11.639 --> 01:14.475
Got the "Newsreaders" crew here.
Hi, Mom.

01:14.542 --> 01:16.210
(Louis)
'"Newsreaders" set out'

01:16.277 --> 01:19.280
'to document
this historic final episode.'

01:19.347 --> 01:21.882
'But what we actually found
may surprise you.'

01:21.949 --> 01:23.117
'Action.'

01:23.184 --> 01:25.153
If he dies, let it be
on your conscience.

01:25.219 --> 01:28.622
You mean, I'm not gonna get
in any real trouble if he dies.

01:28.689 --> 01:30.491
If you can live with yourself,
afterward.

01:30.558 --> 01:34.027
Yeah, sure, totally.
Up top.

01:34.094 --> 01:35.796
I'm sorry, David?
Can we cut?

01:35.863 --> 01:38.499
I-I can't remember which hand
Blake uses to do things.

01:38.566 --> 01:41.335
Well, which hand
do you use?

01:41.402 --> 01:43.737
Blake would use
the hand you use.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.606
'Are you right-handed
or are you left-handed?'

01:45.673 --> 01:47.875
I'm sorry.
I'm just really confused.

01:47.941 --> 01:50.578
(Louis)
'But before there was the
"Childrens Hospital" of today'

01:50.644 --> 01:54.715
'there was this pilot that was
made originally for daytime TV''

01:54.782 --> 01:57.551
'It never made it to air,
but it contained the DNA'

01:57.618 --> 01:59.653
'of what the show
would eventually become.'

01:59.720 --> 02:02.055
You're both damn good doctors...
and lovers.

02:02.122 --> 02:04.192
But I have to fire one of you.

02:04.258 --> 02:06.126
- No, Chief.
- Chief, no.

02:06.194 --> 02:09.096
I actually play the role of,
uh, both twins.

02:09.163 --> 02:12.600
Stop and we'll just switch the,
uh...switch it over.

02:12.666 --> 02:15.269
- Okay, good.
- Quickly, please.

02:15.336 --> 02:17.037
'This is the 1960s', guys.'

02:17.104 --> 02:20.708
In fact, as soon as anybody
opens their mouth on a TV show

02:20.774 --> 02:22.943
you've to pay them
a lot more money.

02:23.010 --> 02:24.378
Isn't that right, Jay?

02:24.445 --> 02:27.415
But some people were
lucky enough to get lines.

02:27.481 --> 02:29.250
Fifteen seasons worth.

02:29.317 --> 02:31.419
'The cast
of "Childrens Hospital".'

02:31.485 --> 02:34.988
None of us knew it would get
so big so fast, did we?

02:35.055 --> 02:38.692
It was like a runaway train with
its head cut off, wasn't it?

02:38.759 --> 02:42.162
I couldn't walk down the street
...without being mobbed.

02:42.230 --> 02:44.898
I had to walk down
through neighborhoods

02:44.965 --> 02:46.800
where mostly
blind people lived

02:46.867 --> 02:49.069
so I could have some peace
while walking.

02:49.136 --> 02:50.137
[foreign language]

02:50.204 --> 02:51.805
[foreign language translated]

02:51.872 --> 02:54.442
It's hard for me
because I don't speak English.

02:54.508 --> 02:57.378
Fans think that because I learn
all of my lines phonetically

02:57.445 --> 03:00.281
I understand them
when they make sex talk at me.

03:00.348 --> 03:02.383
I only kind of do.

03:05.586 --> 03:07.621
You're gorgeous,
you know that.

03:09.323 --> 03:12.326
'You're gorgeous.'

03:12.393 --> 03:13.861
Very beautiful.

03:15.963 --> 03:17.598
By the end of the first season

03:17.665 --> 03:20.067
"Childrens Hospital"
was a bonafide hit.

03:20.133 --> 03:23.237
But even as these gorgeous
doctors were breaking hearts

03:23.304 --> 03:25.506
the show itself was
breaking new ground.

03:25.573 --> 03:27.841
'Such as this scene
from season four.'

03:27.908 --> 03:31.879
'The first time a doctor
was portrayed on television'

03:31.945 --> 03:33.146
'by a woman.'

03:33.213 --> 03:34.648
Oh! Sorry, nurse.

03:34.715 --> 03:37.017
We thought the new doctor
was coming in.

03:37.084 --> 03:38.319
She did just come in.

03:38.386 --> 03:41.188
First of all, you
mean, "he" just came in.

03:41.255 --> 03:42.423
And where is he?

03:42.490 --> 03:45.659
No. I definitely
did not mean "he".

03:47.728 --> 03:50.364
What are you
talking about, nurse?

03:50.431 --> 03:51.799
Uh, what is
your name again?

03:51.865 --> 03:56.236
The name is Lola Spratt,
Dr. Lola Spratt.

03:59.740 --> 04:01.309
Righteous!

04:01.375 --> 04:03.777
(Louis)
'And "Childrens Hospital"
would popularize'

04:03.844 --> 04:06.714
'more than just
the catch phrase "Righteous!"'

04:06.780 --> 04:09.517
'The show had become
a global phenomenon.'

04:09.583 --> 04:14.021
'Foreign-language versions were
produced in Canada...Hawaii..'

04:14.087 --> 04:16.857
'...Los Angeles.
Even India.'

04:16.923 --> 04:18.858
[speaking in Hindi]

04:22.062 --> 04:23.997
[Indian music]

04:29.202 --> 04:32.039
'But as the flagship show
reached its late middle age'

04:32.105 --> 04:35.008
'some thought that
the writers had lost touch'

04:35.075 --> 04:37.578
'with their original vision.'

04:37.645 --> 04:39.680
'The story lines
became convoluted.'

04:39.747 --> 04:41.549
Everyone relax.
The tornado has passed.

04:41.615 --> 04:45.353
We may be trapped here for
a while, but help is on the way.

04:45.419 --> 04:46.920
My water just broke.

04:46.987 --> 04:49.056
- I'm gonna have a nephew.
- What?

04:49.122 --> 04:50.791
[hammering]

04:51.892 --> 04:53.527
'Who are you?'

04:53.594 --> 04:55.663
We're the Boom
Town Break dance Troupe.

04:55.729 --> 04:58.732
We're in town for a show
and decided to stop by.

04:58.799 --> 05:01.168
Looks like you guys
could use some help.

05:01.234 --> 05:03.637
[hip-hop music]

05:05.706 --> 05:08.576
'In a creative lull,
the cast and crew became'

05:08.642 --> 05:11.712
disillusioned and bored,
culminating in the now-infamous

05:11.779 --> 05:14.582
scandal that would mark
the beginning of the end

05:14.648 --> 05:16.817
of "Childrens Hospital,"
as well as

05:16.884 --> 05:19.587
the end of the
middle of our news story.

05:19.653 --> 05:22.623
Tell me about the scandal.

05:22.690 --> 05:24.458
Well, you can listen
to the tabloids

05:24.525 --> 05:26.494
but here's my side of the story.

05:26.560 --> 05:31.499
[sighs]
I was trading derivatives in
Asian markets and rededicating

05:31.565 --> 05:33.300
the returns into
municipal slush funds.

05:33.367 --> 05:36.003
'I was heavy on domestic
commodities, so I was merely'

05:36.069 --> 05:40.073
repurposing the dividends into
auction market preferred stocks.

05:40.140 --> 05:41.742
I messed up.

05:41.809 --> 05:44.211
'To combat the sagging
popularity of the show'

05:44.277 --> 05:48.281
'the producers hired Fred Nunley
a well-known TV veteran'

05:48.348 --> 05:50.050
'who has been
brought in to save'

05:50.117 --> 05:53.053
'many beloved shows
over the last three decades.'

05:53.120 --> 05:55.956
'None of those shows have
made it to another season.'

05:56.023 --> 05:58.992
"Childrens Hospital"
had jumped the shark.

05:59.059 --> 06:01.995
'The show's cancelation was
announced after the first'

06:02.062 --> 06:04.364
'episode of this season.'

06:04.432 --> 06:06.400
How did you all
feel when you knew

06:06.467 --> 06:08.268
the show was coming to an end?

06:08.335 --> 06:09.803
We all had
the same reaction.

06:09.870 --> 06:12.205
You know, which
was, "Thank God".

06:12.272 --> 06:14.074
[women laughing]

06:14.141 --> 06:17.177
'The first person to hear
the news was Dixie Peters'

06:17.244 --> 06:20.814
'who played Dr. Cat Black
up until this season'

06:20.881 --> 06:23.717
'when her character died
unexpectedly in childbirth.'

06:23.784 --> 06:26.119
'Ironically, Ms. Peters
died in real life'

06:26.186 --> 06:29.289
'shortly before taping
this interview.'

06:29.356 --> 06:32.426
The idea of doing another
episode makes me physically ill.

06:32.493 --> 06:34.928
I mean, I'd rather
do anything else.

06:34.995 --> 06:37.097
I'd rather do a fifteen-minute
low budget comedy

06:37.164 --> 06:40.468
for basic cable.
I mean, not literally.

06:40.534 --> 06:43.637
I watched all my friends
skyrocket to stardom

06:43.704 --> 06:46.339
while I was stuck,
day in and day out.

06:46.406 --> 06:47.941
Year after year,
on this show.

06:48.008 --> 06:51.311
'Just Falcon
joined the cast in 1993.'

06:51.378 --> 06:54.314
I was offered
"Crocodile Dundee".

06:54.381 --> 06:59.720
But they kept me locked into my
contract, so three sequels later

06:59.787 --> 07:02.422
my very good friend Paul Hogan
is a former millionaire.

07:02.490 --> 07:03.857
The answer to
your question is

07:03.924 --> 07:06.326
yes, we are all
best friends in real life.

07:06.393 --> 07:07.561
[everybody sighs]

07:07.628 --> 07:09.029
[foreign language translated]

07:09.096 --> 07:11.599
"The man that plays
the clown makes me sad."

07:11.665 --> 07:13.867
(Louis
'On the surface, filming
this last episode was'

07:13.934 --> 07:15.836
'just like another
day at the office.'

07:15.903 --> 07:18.739
'Even if tensions
were running a little high.'

07:18.806 --> 07:22.643
I don't care if it's
your birthday. You quit sulking!

07:22.710 --> 07:24.211
"I am a doctor. "

07:24.277 --> 07:25.913
'Yet, no one would speak about'

07:25.979 --> 07:29.149
'the 200-pound
gorilla in the room.'

07:29.216 --> 07:32.019
This is a very difficult
time for you, isn't it?

07:32.085 --> 07:33.887
No.

07:33.954 --> 07:36.790
'Unwilling to let go after
fifteen years on the show'

07:36.857 --> 07:40.293
'Cutter Spindell organized
protests to the network.'

07:40.360 --> 07:42.963
But I guess it didn't work.

07:43.030 --> 07:45.633
I know I've only been
working here a few months

07:45.699 --> 07:48.536
but already, you all
feel like family to me.

07:48.602 --> 07:52.372
I'm gonna miss this place..

07:52.439 --> 07:54.708
...more than you know.

07:54.775 --> 07:56.910
[instrumental music]

07:58.746 --> 08:01.048
More than you'll ever know.

08:06.386 --> 08:09.256
Hello?

08:09.322 --> 08:11.091
Doctors?

08:11.158 --> 08:13.393
